    "body": "\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nTileLang previously lowered `T.access_ptr(...)` to one of two existing TIR patterns:\r\n\r\n- `tir.address_of(BufferLoad(...))`\r\n  - Pros: keeps the original `BufferLoad`.\r\n  - Cons: does not carry explicit access intent / scope metadata (read vs write), which forces downstream passes to be conservative (e.g. inserting sync even when a narrower access footprint would be legal).\r\n- `tir.builtin.tvm_access_ptr(dtype, data, offset, extent, rw_mask)`\r\n  - Pros: carries `rw_mask` and `extent`.\r\n  - Cons: drops the original `BufferLoad` and therefore loses indexing/stride context. This breaks expectations in passes that rely on the buffer access structure (e.g. “safe memory access” legalization), and `tvm_access_ptr` is not desired to appear in the frontend IR.\r\n\r\nTo resolve this mismatch, TileLang introduces a dedicated frontend-only op that preserves both:\r\n\r\n- the **structured buffer access** (`BufferLoad`) and\r\n- the **access intent** (`rw_mask` + `extent`).\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n### 1) New TileLang Op: `tl.access_ptr(base_load, extent, rw_mask)`\r\n\r\nA new TileLang-only intrinsic is registered and used as the frontend representation of `T.access_ptr`:\r\n\r\n- **Op name:** `tl.access_ptr`\r\n- **Signature:**\r\n  - `arg0`: `tir.BufferLoad` (`base_load`)\r\n  - `arg1`: 1D extent in **elements** (`extent`)\r\n  - `arg2`: access mask (`rw_mask`): `1=read`, `2=write`, `3=read-write`\r\n- **Effect kind:** pure (metadata-only)\r\n\r\nFiles:\r\n\r\n- `src/op/builtin.h`\r\n- `src/op/builtin.cc`\r\n\r\n### 2) Frontend `T.access_ptr` now emits `tl.access_ptr`\r\n\r\n`tilelang/language/builtin.py` was updated so `T.access_ptr(...)` no longer dispatches to\r\n`tir.address_of(...)` or `tir.builtin.tvm_access_ptr(...)`. Instead it creates:\r\n\r\n```python\r\ntir.call_intrin(\r\n    \"handle\",\r\n    tir.op.Op.get(\"tl.access_ptr\"),\r\n    base_load,     # BufferLoad\r\n    extent_1d,     # PrimExpr\r\n    rw_mask,       # IntImm(int32)\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nKey frontend semantics:\r\n\r\n- The first argument is always a `BufferLoad`, so downstream passes can recover:\r\n  - the referenced `tir.Buffer`\r\n  - strides (explicit `buffer->strides` if present, otherwise row-major)\r\n  - storage scope / layout metadata associated with the buffer\r\n- Extent defaults follow typical pointer intent:\r\n  - `BufferLoad` base: `extent = 1` (element pointer)\r\n  - `BufferRegion` base: `extent = product(region.extents)`\r\n  - `Buffer` base: `extent = product(buffer.shape)`\r\n- `ignore_last_ndim` is implemented by zeroing the trailing indices in the emitted `BufferLoad`.\r\n- `offset != 0` is only supported for **1D** bases when emitting `tl.access_ptr` (for N-D, users should express the offset via indexing, e.g. `A[i + off, j]`).\r\n\r\nFile:\r\n\r\n- `tilelang/language/builtin.py`\r\n\r\n### 3) New lowering pass: `tl.transform.LowerAccessPtr`\r\n\r\nTo keep interoperability with downstream infrastructure that expects\r\n`tir.builtin.tvm_access_ptr`, TileLang adds a dedicated lowering pass:\r\n\r\n- Rewrites:\r\n  - `tl.access_ptr(BufferLoad(buf, indices), extent, rw_mask)`\r\n  - into:\r\n  - `tir.builtin.tvm_access_ptr(dtype, buf.data, linear_offset, extent, rw_mask)`\r\n- `linear_offset` computation:\r\n  - uses `buffer->strides` when defined (and matches ndim)\r\n  - otherwise falls back to row-major strides from `buffer->shape`\r\n  - for vector indices (e.g. `Ramp`, `Broadcast`), uses the base/value to derive a conservative base offset\r\n\r\nFiles:\r\n\r\n- `src/transform/lower_access_ptr.cc`\r\n- `tilelang/transform/__init__.py` (Python binding)\r\n\r\n### 4) Compilation pipeline integration\r\n\r\n`LowerAccessPtr` is inserted into the standard TileLang lowering pipeline so that:\r\n\r\n- early passes can still see structured buffer access (`BufferLoad`) for analysis and safety checks\r\n- later stages can operate on standardized `tvm_access_ptr` when needed for codegen patterns\r\n\r\nCurrent placement:\r\n\r\n- immediately after `LegalizeSafeMemoryAccess()`\r\n\r\nFile:\r\n\r\n- `tilelang/engine/phase.py`\r\n\r\n### 5) Compatibility updates in existing passes\r\n\r\nSome existing passes/utilities previously assumed all pointer metadata would appear as\r\n`tvm_access_ptr` (or `address_of`). They were extended to also accept `tl.access_ptr`:\r\n\r\n- `src/op/operator.cc`\r\n  - `GetVarFromAccessPtr(...)` now supports extracting the underlying `Var` from `tl.access_ptr`\r\n- `src/transform/lower_tile_op.cc`\r\n  - permuted-layout and related pointer rewrite logic now recognizes `tl.access_ptr`\r\n  - avoids hard failures for `T.access_ptr(...)` under layout transformations\r\n- `src/transform/loop_vectorize.cc`\r\n  - atomic-add dtype inference accepts `tl.access_ptr` as the destination pointer argument\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\nTests were updated/added to reflect the new frontend shape and the explicit lowering step:\r\n\r\n- `testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_access_ptr.py`\r\n  - verifies `T.access_ptr(...)` builds `tl.access_ptr(BufferLoad, extent, rw_mask)`\r\n  - verifies `tilelang.transform.LowerAccessPtr()` rewrites to `tir.tvm_access_ptr` with expected `offset/extent`\r\n- `testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_access_ptr_codegen.py`\r\n  - smoke-test: `T.access_ptr -> tl.access_ptr -> tvm_access_ptr -> cp.async` remains codegen-able on CUDA\r\n\r\n",
